The paper deals with the problem of identifying errors in predictive models, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The methodology proposed in the paper involves organizing data based on feature similarity and confidence scores, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the need for input from an oracle to identify errors, which is a common topic in computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE).
